      </p>
     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d239n1-ptr" id="PJA08d239n1">1</a>
      <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> had become convinced that the ports of Cadiz and Bilbao were the best means for sending and receiving correspondence with America when, on or about 12 Feb., he received <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Abigail Adams (17441818), m. John Adams 1764 ]">AA</abbr>s letter of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-03-02-0185" class="document">10 Dec. 1779</a> via Cadiz (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Adams Family Correspondence,&lt;/i&gt; ed. L. H. Butterfield and others, Cambridge, 1963 ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Adams Family Correspondence</span></span>, 3:<a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-03-02-0211" class="document">271272</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-03-02-0213" class="document">275</a>).</p>
